RED STAR TOWING & TRANSPORTATION COMPANY, as Owner of THE Coal Barge RED STAR NO. 17 and Walter F. Roberts, as Captain of Said Barge, Libelants-Appellees, v. THE Steam Tug WYOMISSING, Her Engines, etc., and The Reading Company, Claimant-Appellant, and consolidated causes. No. 302. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 4, 1932. Macklin, Brown, Lenahan & Speer, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), fon appellant. Single and Single and George B. Warbur-ton, all of New York City (Thomas*H. Middleton, of New York City, of counsel), for Red Star Towing & Transp. Co. Thomas A. McDonald, of New York City, for libelant-appellee Weston-Dodson & Co., Inc.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed,
